The Associate, Polling & Analytics will provide support for a growing team that uses data strategically to inform progressive campaigns across the entire organization, all of which are dedicated to producing a more just and inclusive economy and democracy. The Hub Project maintains a robust pipeline of polling, data, and analytics projects, and as the Polling & Analytics Associate, you will assist with the execution of those projects, which includes:

Development and quality control checks of products throughout the research lifecycle, including requests for proposal, qualitative discussion guides, survey questionnaires, memos, and presentations.
Maintaining awareness of and communicating key public opinion trends to the full Polling & Analytics team and other internal teams at The Hub Project.
Collaborating with our communications team to review documents for public opinion products for public release (e.g., press releases, media advisories, and/or op-eds).
Assisting in data analysis to create meaningful and actionable recommendations and insights shared across campaign teams within the organization.
Working with external vendors and consultants to manage scheduling, contracts, and invoices.
Perform other duties as assigned.


Salary: Not listed

Location: Washington, DC


[See more and apply here](https://thehubproject.org/associate-polling-director-analytics/)
